<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>8. Routing Data on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/8-routing-data/</link><description>Recent content in 8. Routing Data on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/8-routing-data/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>8.1 Configure the Routing Connector</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/8-routing-data/8-1-connector/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/8-routing-data/8-1-connector/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In this exercise, you will configure the &lt;strong&gt;Routing Connector&lt;/strong&gt; in the &lt;code&gt;gateway.yaml&lt;/code&gt; file. This setup enables the &lt;code&gt;gateway&lt;/code&gt; to route traces based on the &lt;code&gt;deployment.environment&lt;/code&gt; attribute in the spans you send. By implementing this, you can process and handle traces differently depending on their attributes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In OpenTelemetry configuration files, &lt;code&gt;connectors&lt;/code&gt; have their own dedicated section, similar to receivers and processors.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>8.2 Configuring the Pipelines</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/8-routing-data/8-2-pipelines/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/8-routing-data/8-2-pipelines/</guid><description>&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update the &lt;code&gt;traces&lt;/code&gt; pipeline to use routing&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To enable &lt;code&gt;routing&lt;/code&gt;, update the original &lt;code&gt;traces:&lt;/code&gt; pipeline by using &lt;code&gt;routing&lt;/code&gt; as the only exporter. This ensures all span data is sent through the routing connector for evaluation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remove all processors and replace it with an empty array (&lt;code&gt;[]&lt;/code&gt;). These are now defined in the &lt;code&gt;traces/standard&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;traces/security&lt;/code&gt; pipelines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;yaml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-yaml" data-lang="yaml"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;pipelines&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;traces&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Original traces pipeline&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;receivers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;- &lt;span class="l"&gt;otlp &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# OTLP Receiver&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;processors&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nt"&gt;exporters&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;- &lt;span class="l"&gt;routing &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Routing Connector&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Add both the &lt;code&gt;standard&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;security&lt;/code&gt; traces pipelines&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>8.3 Test Routing Connector</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/8-routing-data/8-3-test-routing/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/ninja-workshops/foundations/3-opentelemetry-collector-workshops/2-advanced-collector-old/8-routing-data/8-3-test-routing/</guid><description>&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this section, we will test the &lt;code&gt;routing&lt;/code&gt; rule configured for the &lt;strong&gt;Gateway&lt;/strong&gt;. The expected result is that the&lt;code&gt;span&lt;/code&gt; generated by the &lt;code&gt;loadgen&lt;/code&gt; will be sent to the &lt;code&gt;gateway-traces-security.out&lt;/code&gt; file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start the Gateway&lt;/strong&gt;: In your &lt;strong&gt;Gateway terminal&lt;/strong&gt; window start the &lt;code&gt;gateway&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;../otelcol --config gateway.yaml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start the Agent&lt;/strong&gt;: In your &lt;strong&gt;Agent terminal&lt;/strong&gt; window start the &lt;code&gt;agent&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code-block"&gt;
 &lt;div class="code-block__header"&gt;
 &lt;span class="code-block__file"&gt;&lt;span class="code-block__lang"&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;button class="code-block__copy" type="button" aria-label="Copy code to clipboard"&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;../otelcol --config agent.yaml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Send a Regular Span&lt;/strong&gt;: In the &lt;strong&gt;Spans terminal&lt;/strong&gt; window send a regular span using the &lt;code&gt;loadgen&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>